{
  "texts": [
    "Moreover, the code generated by LLM might converge to a single solution, thereby limiting the model's capacity for generalization [26].",
    "To address these limitations and generate more diverse training data that can adapt to a broader range of domains, one potential improvement is to incorporate continuous learning mutation operators.",
    "These operators can track changes in the problem space and introduce multiple initial solutions, facilitating multiple restarts of the search process.",
    "Additionally, by recording the mutations produced by each mutation operator and providing rewards or penalties based on the performance of the mutated offspring, the operators can also learn higher-quality mutation patterns.Another approach type focuses on leveraging LLM's code generation capabilities and EA's search framework to continuously enhance code generation [19], [49]- [51].",
    "However, these methods encounter difficulties when dealing with complex algorithmic logic [50]."
  ]
}